questions.text: What subjects do you enjoy most in school?
questions.answer: I really enjoy Math, Computer Science, and Physics. I find problem-solving in these subjects very satisfying.

questions.text: What activities make you lose track of time?
questions.answer: Coding personal projects, especially when I'm working on algorithms or building web applications. I also love analyzing data to find patterns.

questions.text: Do you prefer working with people, data, or things?
questions.answer: I really enjoy working with data and building things, but I also like collaborating with others on projects. I think I prefer a mix.

questions.text: What type of work environment appeals to you?
questions.answer: I'd like a hybrid environment with some remote flexibility. I enjoy the energy of working with a team in person, but also value focused time at home.

questions.text: How important is work-life balance to you?
questions.answer: Very important. I want to have time for personal projects, hobbies, and spending time with family and friends.

questions.text: What programming languages or technologies are you most excited to learn more about?
questions.answer: I'm really interested in Python for machine learning and data science. I've also been exploring React for web development.

questions.text: When you work on projects, do you prefer to focus on the technical implementation or the user experience?
questions.answer: I think I lean more toward the technical implementation, but I understand that user experience is crucial for any successful product.
